If you crawl such an HTML page with a standard configuration and proper 
scope, Heritrix will find and crawl that link. The server-side language 
with which it was generated or any file-extension visible in the URL is 
irrelevant.

So, the problem must be in your configuration or code.

Note that getOutlinks() only returns links discovered by the Extractors 
until the LinksScoper is applied. The LinksScoper converts all links 
that pass scope-testing into CrawlURIs, and puts them in the 
&#39;outcandidates&#39; collection, clearing the outlinks collection.

So maybe your scope is rejecting the link, or you are looking for it too 
late in processing.

Also, maybe your test page has some other problem that prevents the 
content from being recognized as HTML. (Perhaps a bad Content-Type or 
other header?)

- Gordon @ IA

